sp.p:
Sir, your Muses have no such water I assure you; 
your Nectar, or the Iuice of your Nepenthe is nothing to it; it is 
above your Metheglin, beleeue it.

Louing?  it were pitty I should be liuing else, beleeue 
me.  Saue you Sir.  Saue you sweete Lady, Saue you Mounsieur Anaides; 
Saue you deare Madame.

Sir we will acknowledge your seruice doubt not; 
henceforth you shall be no more Asotus to us, but our Golde-Finch, 
and we your Cages.
